Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Active Energy Measurement Integrated Circuits (ICs) Market

Active energy measurement integrated circuits (ICs) market is expected to reach USD 91,018.63 million by 2028 witnessing market growth at a rate of 9.10% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on active energy measurement integrated circuits (ICs) market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth.

Energy measurement is the measurement of consumption of energy, which is used to assess consumer requirement, which is helpful in better energy management. Advances of technology of energy calculation results in the replacement of conventional utility metres. Demand for high-precision electrical metres from different applications, such as commercial or manufacturing industries, is growing and driving the need for intelligent management. The demand for energy calculation ICs has seen a constant need for ICs that are smart enough to calculate the total use of electrical power.

Increasing demand for high accuracy electric meters from various applications such as commercial or manufacturing industries, increasing adoption of smart appliances, surging levels of investment for the development and innovation in energy measurement technology, growing number of government regulations for energy utilization, rising preferences towards the usages of smart meters which record the consumption of electric energy and transfer the information to the supplier for monitoring and billing the energy usage of the customer are some of the major as well as vital factors which will likely to augment the growth of the active energy measurement integrated circuits (ICs) market in the projected timeframe of 2021-2028. On the other hand, increasing adoption of new and advanced technologies which offer various features in energy meters including measurement and monitoring along with rising trends of energy measurement to calculate reactive energy measurement, power quality monitoring, and multi-tariff billing which will further contribute by generating massive opportunities that will lead to the growth of the active energy measurement integrated circuits (ICs) market in the above mentioned projected timeframe.

High cost of the product along with difficult to fabricate an IC with low noise which will likely to act as market restraints factor for the growth of the active energy measurement integrated circuits (ICs) in the above mentioned projected timeframe. Large value of saturation resistance of transistors will become the biggest and foremost challenge for the growth of the market.

